@title A market for NFTs on Minted.
 @dev This top level file holds no data directly to ease future upgrades.

@notice Called once to configure the contract after the initial deployment.
 @dev This farms the initialize call out to inherited contracts as needed.
@notice Allows Minted to update the market configuration.

@dev Checks who the seller for an NFT is, this will check escrow or return the current owner if not in escrow.
 This is a no-op function required to avoid compile errors.

@title A market for NFTs on Minted.
 @dev This top level file holds no data directly to ease future upgrades.

@notice Called once to configure the contract after the initial deployment.
 @dev This farms the initialize call out to inherited contracts as needed.
@notice Allows Minted to update the market configuration.

@dev Checks who the seller for an NFT is, this will check escrow or return the current owner if not in escrow.
 This is a no-op function required to avoid compile errors.

devdoc.details: This top level file holds no data directly to ease future upgrades.

_getFees(address,uint256,address,uint256.details: Calculates how funds should be distributed for the given sale details. If this is a primary sale, the creator revenue will appear as `ownerRev`.

getFees(address,uint256,uint256).details: This could be used to present exact fee distributing on listing or before a bid is placed.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

initialize(address,address).details: This farms the initialize call out to inherited contracts as needed.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

devdoc.title: A market for NFTs on Minted.

adminUpdateConfig(uint256,uint256,uint25.notice: Allows Minted to update the market configuration.

getFeeConfig().notice: Returns the current fee configuration in basis points.

getFees(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Returns how funds will be distributed for a sale at the given price point.

getIsPrimary(address,uint256).notice: Returns true if the given NFT has not been sold in this market previously and is being sold by the creator.

getMintedTreasury().notice: Returns the address of the Minted treasury.

getPendingWithdrawal(address).notice: Returns how much funds are available for manual withdraw due to failed transfers.

initialize(address,address).notice: Called once to configure the contract after the initial deployment.

withdraw().notice: Allows a user to manually withdraw funds which originally failed to transfer.
